item.title: 525/508/562/569 Compile help!
item.dc:creator: @Manu0238 Manu0238
item.description:
@Manu0238 wrote:

Ok Download the Java JDk , install it and you should have the version 20 then replace the text in your compiler with this:

@echo off title Compile All cd ../src "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/players/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/players/update/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/players/items/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/players/combat/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/io/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/io/packets/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/net/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/util/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/world/mapdata/*.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/world/items/*.java msg * Complete echo Press Enter Now pause

If you already had java JDK 20 then the 5 was wrong it must be 6.

item.title: 525/508/562/569 Compile help!
item.dc:creator: @Manu0238 Manu0238
item.description:
@Manu0238 wrote:

actually it doesnt matter which version you download.

Try this link http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/widget/jdk6.jsp
IF this link doesnt work use this link http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp and select Download JDK

Make a rigth click on your compiler and add this “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_YOUR_JDK_VERSION\bin\javac.exe” -cp . -d …/bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/*.java

This is just an example , this is out of my compiler.
But it doesnt matter which jdk you use.

Btw this is out of a 508 send me your compiling text (rigth click select edit and send me the text)
